<section xml:id="loops-strings_vocabulary">
<title>Vocabulary</title>
<ul>
<li>
<title>loop:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>loop</h></idx>
A statement that executes a sequence of statements repeatedly.</p></li>
<li>
<title>loop body:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>loop body</h></idx>
The statements inside the loop.</p></li>
<li>
<title>infinite loop:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>infinite loop</h></idx>
A loop whose condition is always true.</p></li>
<li>
<title>increment:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>increment</h></idx>
Increase the value of a variable.</p></li>
<li>
<title>decrement:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>decrement</h></idx>
Decrease the value of a variable.</p></li>
<li>
<title>iteration:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>iteration</h></idx>
Executing a sequence of statements repeatedly.</p></li>
<li>
<title>loop variable:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>loop variable</h></idx>
A variable that is initialized, tested, and updated in order to control a loop.</p></li>
<li>
<title>index:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>index</h></idx>
An integer variable or value used to indicate a character in a string.</p></li>
<li>
<title>Unicode:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>Unicode</h></idx>
An international standard for representing characters in most of the world's languages.</p></li>
<li>
<title>empty string:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>empty string</h></idx>
The string <c>""</c>, which contains no characters and has a length of zero.</p></li>
<li>
<title>overloaded:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>overloaded</h></idx>
Two or more methods with the same name but different parameters.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
